obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9008)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9008&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[Short title, extent, application and commencement].--(1) This Act may be called the Right of`
  line `Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act, 2009.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Subject to the provisions of articles 29 and 30 of the Constitution, the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `apply to conferment of rights on children to free and compulsory education.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in this Act shall apply to Madrasas, Vedic Pathsalas and educational`
  line `institutions primarily imparting religious instruction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2018, s. 3 and The Second Schedule, for "the marginal heading" (w.e.f. 5-1-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `3. 1st April, 2010, vide notification No. S.O. 428(E), dated 16th February, 2010, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 30 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-8- 2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9009)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9009&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a school established, owned or controlled by the Central Government, or the`
  line `administrator of the Union territory, having no legislature, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a school, other than the school referred to in sub-clause (i), established`
  line `within the territory of--`
  line
  line `(A) a State, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(B) a Union territory having legislature, the Government of that Union territory;`
  line
  line `(b) "capitation fee" means any kind of donation or contribution or payment other than the fee`
  line `notified by the school;`
  line
  line `(c) "child" means a male or female child of the age of six to fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(d) "child belonging to disadvantaged group" means ^3`
  line `[a child with disability or] a child belonging`
  line `to the Scheduled Caste, the Scheduled Tribe, the socially and educationally backward class or such`
  line `other group having disadvantage owing to social, cultural, economical, geographical, linguistic,`
  line `gender or such other factor, as may be specified by the appropriate Government, by notification;`
  line
  line `(e) "child belonging to weaker section" means a child belonging to such parent or guardian whose`
  line `annual income is lower than the minimum limit specified by the appropriate Government, by`
  line notification;
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ee) "child with disability" includes,--`
  line
  line `(A) a child with "disability" as defined in clause (i) of section 2 of the Persons with`
  line `Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995`
  line `(1 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(B) a child, being a person with disability as defined in clause (j) of section 2 of the National`
  line `Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple`
  line `Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999);`
  line
  line `(C) a child with "severe disability" as defined in clause (o) of section 2 of the National Trust`
  line `for Welfare of Persons with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities`
  line `Act, 1999 (44 of 1999).]`
  line
  line `(f) "elementary education" means the education from first class to eighth class;`
  line
  line `(g) "guardian", in relation to a child, means a person having the care and custody of that child and`
  line `includes a natural guardian or guardian appointed or declared by a court or a statute;`
  line
  line `(h) "local authority" means a Municipal Corporation or Municipal Council or Zila Parishad or`
  line `Nagar Panchayat or Panchayat, by whatever name called, and includes such other authority or body`
  line `having administrative control over the school or empowered by or under any law for the time being in`
  line `force to function as a local authority in any city, town or village;`
  line
  line `(i) "National Commission for Protection of Child Rights" means the National Commission for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights constituted under section 3 of the Commissions for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006);`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "parent" means either the natural or step or adoptive father or mother of a child;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "Schedule" means the Schedule annexed to this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "school" means any recognised school imparting elementary education and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a school established, owned or controlled by the appropriate Government or a local`
  line authority;
  line
  line `(ii) an aided school receiving aid or grants to meet whole or part of its expenses from the`
  line `appropriate Government or the local authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) a school belonging to specified category; and`
  line
  line `(iv) an unaided school not receiving any kind of aid or grants to meet its expenses from the`
  line `appropriate Government or the local authority;`
  line
  line `(o) "screening procedure" means the method of selection for admission of a child, in preference`
  line `over another, other than a random method;`
  line
  line `(p) "specified category", in relation to a school, means a school known as Kendriya Vidyalaya,`
  line `Navodaya Vidyalaya, Sainik School or any other school having a distinct character which may be`
  line `specified, by notification, by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(q) 'State Commission for Protection of Child Rights" means the State Commission for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights constituted under section 3 of the Commissions for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9010)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Right of child to free and compulsory education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9010&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Every child of the age of six to fourteen`
  line `years, including a child referred to in clause (d) or clause (e) of section 2, shall have the right to free and`
  line `compulsory education in a neighbourhood school till the completion of his or her elementary education.]`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), no child shall be liable to pay any kind of fee or charges or`
  line `expenses which may prevent him or her from pursuing and completing the elementary education.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^3
  line `(3) A child with disability referred to in sub-clause (A) of clause (ee) of section 2 shall, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal Opportunities, Protection of Rights and`
  line `Full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996), and a child referred to in sub-clauses (B) and (C) of clause (ee)`
  line `of section 2, have the same rights to pursue free and compulsory elementary education which children`
  line `with disabilities have under the provisions of Chapter V of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal`
  line `Opportunities, Protection of Rights and Full Participation) Act, 1995:`
  line
  line `Provided that a child with "multiple disabilities" referred to in clause (h) and a child with "severe`
  line `disability" referred to in clause (o) of section 2 of the National Trust for Welfare of Persons with Autism,`
  line `Cerebral Palsy, Mental Retardation and Multiple Disabilities Act, 1999 (44 of 1999) may also have the`
  line `right to opt for home-based education.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 2012, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-8-2012)`
  line
  line `2. Proviso omitted by Act 30 of 2012, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9011)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Special provisions for children not admitted to, or who have not completed, elementary education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9011&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Where a child above six years of age has not been admitted in any school or though`
  line `admitted, could not complete his or her elementary education, then, he or she shall be admitted in a class`
  line `appropriate to his or her age:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a child is directly admitted in a class appropriate to his or her age, then, he or she`
  line `shall, in order to be at par with others, have a right to receive special training, in such manner, and within`
  line `such time-limits, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a child so admitted to elementary education shall be entitled to free education`
  line `till completion of elementary education even after fourteen years.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9012)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Right of transfer to other school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9012&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in a school, there is no provision for completion of`
  line `elementary education, a child shall have a right to seek transfer to any other school, excluding the school`
  line `specified in sub-clauses (iii) and (iv) of clause (n) of section 2, for completing his or her elementary`
  line education.
  line
  line `(2) Where a child is required to move from one school to another, either within a State or outside, for`
  line `any reason whatsoever, such child shall have a right to seek transfer to any other school, excluding the`
  line `school specified in sub-clauses (iii) and (iv) of clause (n) of section 2, for completing his or her`
  line `elementary education.`
  line
  line `(3) For seeking admission in such other school, the Head-teacher or in-charge of the school where`
  line `such child was last admitted, shall immediately issue the transfer certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that delay in producing transfer certificate shall not be a ground for either delaying or`
  line `denying admission in such other school:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Head-teacher or in-charge of the school delaying issuance of transfer`
  line `certificate shall be liable for disciplinary action under the service rules applicable to him or her.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9013)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Duty of appropriate Government and local authority to establish school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9013&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For carrying out the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the appropriate Government and the local authority shall establish, within such`
  line `area or limits of neighbourhood, as may be prescribed, a school, where it is not so established, within a`
  line `period of three years from the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9014)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Sharing of financial and other responsibilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9014&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government and the State`
  line `Governments shall have concurrent responsibility for providing funds for carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall prepare the estimates of capital and recurring expenditure for the`
  line `implementation of the provisions of the Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall provide to the State Governments, as grants-in-aid of revenues,`
  line `such percentage of expenditure referred to in sub-section (2) as it may determine, from time to time, in`
  line `consultation with the State Governments.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may make a request to the President to make a reference to the Finance`
  line `Commission under sub-clause (d) of clause (3) of article 280 to examine the need for additional resources`
  line `to be provided to any State Government so that the said State Government may provide its share of funds`
  line `for carrying out the provisions of the Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), the State Government shall, taking into`
  line `consideration the sums provided by the Central Government to a State Government under sub-section (3),`
  line `and its other resources, be responsible to provide funds for implementation of the provisions of the Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall--`
  line
  line `(a) develop a framework of national curriculum with the help of academic authority specified`
  line `under section 29;`
  line
  line `(b) develop and enforce standards for training of teachers;`
  line
  line `(c) provide technical support and resources to the State Government for promoting innovations,`
  line `researches, planning and capacity building.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9015)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duties of appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9015&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall`
  line
  line `(a) provide free and compulsory elementary education to every child:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a child is admitted by his or her parents or guardian, as the case may be, in a`
  line `school other than a school established, owned, controlled or substantially financed by funds provided`
  line `directly or indirectly by the appropriate Government or a local authority, such child or his or her`
  line `parents or guardian, as the case may be, shall not be entitled to make a claim for reimbursement of`
  line `expenditure incurred on elementary education of the child in such other school.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --The term compulsory education means obligation of the appropriate`
  line `Government to--`
  line
  line `(i) provide free elementary education to every child of the age of six to fourteen years; and`
  line
  line `(ii) ensure compulsory admission, attendance and completion of elementary education by`
  line `every child of the age of six to fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(b) ensure availability of a neighbourhood school as specified in section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) ensure that the child belonging to weaker section and the child belonging to disadvantaged`
  line `group are not discriminated against and prevented from pursuing and completing elementary`
  line `education on any grounds;`
  line
  line `(d) provide infrastructure including school building, teaching staff and learning equipment;`
  line
  line `(e) provide special training facility specified in section 4;`
  line
  line `(f) ensure and monitor admission, attendance and completion of elementary education by every`
  line child;
  line
  line `(g) ensure good quality elementary education conforming to the standards and norms specified in`
  line `the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(h) ensure timely prescribing of curriculum and courses of study for elementary education; and`
  line
  line `(i) provide training facility for teachers.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 8, Central Act No. 35 of 2009.After the existing clause (ii) of the`
  line `explanation to clause (a) of section 8 of the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act,`
  line 7
  line `2009 (Central Act No. 35 of 2009), hereinafter in this Act referred to as the principal Act, the following`
  line `new clause shall he added, namely:-`
  line
  line `(iii) ensure achievement of class appropriate learning level by every child of the age of six to`
  line `fourteen years;.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 2017, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9016)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Duties of local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9016&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every local authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) provide free and compulsory elementary education to every child:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a child is admitted by his or her parents or guardian, as the case may be, in a`
  line `school other than a school established, owned, controlled or substantially financed by funds provided directly or indirectly by the appropriate Government or a local authority, such child or his or her`
  line `parents or guardian, as the case may be, shall not be entitled to make a claim for reimbursement of`
  line `expenditure incurred on elementary education of the child in such other school;`
  line
  line `(b) ensure availability of a neighbourhood school as specified in section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) ensure that the child belonging to weaker section and the child belonging to disadvantaged`
  line `group are not discriminated against and prevented from pursuing and completing elementary`
  line `education on any grounds;`
  line
  line `(d) maintain records of children up to the age of fourteen years residing within its jurisdiction, in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(e) ensure and monitor admission, attendance and completion of elementary education by every`
  line `child residing within its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(f) provide infrastructure including school building, teaching staff and learning material;`
  line
  line `(g) provide special training facility specified in section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) ensure good quality elementary education conforming to the standards and norms specified in`
  line `the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(i) ensure timely prescribing of curriculum and courses of study for elementary education;`
  line
  line `(j) provide training facility for teachers;`
  line
  line `(k) ensure admission of children of migrant families;`
  line
  line `(l) monitor functioning of schools within its jurisdiction; and`
  line
  line `(m) decide the academic calendar.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9017)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty of parents and guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9017&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every parent or guardian to admit or`
  line `cause to be admitted his or her child or ward, as the case may be, to an elementary education in the`
  line `neighbourhood school.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9018)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appropriate Government to provide for pre-school education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9018&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `With a view to prepare`
  line `children above the age of three years for elementary education and to provide early childhood care and`
  line `education for all children until they complete the age of six years, the appropriate Government may make`
  line `necessary arrangement for providing free pre-school education for such children.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9019)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Extent of school’s responsibility for free and compulsory education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9019&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of`
  line `this Act, a school,--`
  line
  line `(a) specified in sub-clause (i) of clause (n) of section 2 shall provide free and compulsory`
  line `elementary education to all children admitted therein;`
  line
  line `(b) specified in sub-clause (ii) of clause (n) of section 2 shall provide free and compulsory`
  line `elementary education to such proportion of children admitted therein as its annual recurring aid or`
  line `grants so received bears to its annual recurring expenses, subject to a minimum of twenty-five per`
  line cent.;
  line
  line `(c) specified in sub-clauses (iii) and (iv) of clause (n) of section 2 shall admit in class I, to the`
  line `extent of at least twenty-five per cent. of the strength of that class, children belonging to weaker`
  line `section and disadvantaged group in the neighbourhood and provide free and compulsory elementary`
  line `education till its completion:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a school specified in clause (n) of section 2 imparts pre-school education,`
  line `the provisions of clauses (a) to (c) shall apply for admission to such pre-school education.`
  line
  line `(2) The school specified in sub-clause (iv) of clause (n) of section 2 providing free and compulsory`
  line `elementary education as specified in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be reimbursed expenditure so`
  line `incurred by it to the extent of per-child-expenditure incurred by the State, or the actual amount charged`
  line `from the child, whichever is less, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such reimbursement shall not exceed per-child-expenditure incurred by a school`
  line `specified in sub-clause (i) of clause (n) of section 2:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where such school is already under obligation to provide free education to a`
  line `specified number of children on account of it having received any land, building, equipment or other`
  line `facilities, either free of cost or at a concessional rate, such school shall not be entitled for reimbursement`
  line `to the extent of such obligation.`
  line
  line `(3) Every school shall provide such information as may be required by the appropriate Government or`
  line `the local authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9020)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `No capitation fee and screening procedure for admission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9020&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No school or person shall,`
  line `while admitting a child, collect any capitation fee and subject the child or his or her parents or guardian to`
  line `any screening procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) Any school or person, if in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) receives capitation fee, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ten times the`
  line `capitation fee charged;`
  line
  line `(b) subjects a child to screening procedure, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees for the first contravention and fifty thousand rupees for each subsequent`
  line contraventions.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9021)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Proof of age for admission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9021&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of admission to elementary education, the age`
  line `of a child shall be determined on the basis of the birth certificate issued in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Births, Deaths and Marriages Registration Act, 1886 (6 of 1886) or on the basis of such other`
  line `document, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No child shall be denied admission in a school for lack of age proof.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9022)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `No denial of admission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9022&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A child shall be admitted in a school at the commencement of the`
  line `academic year or within such extended period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no child shall be denied admission if such admission is sought subsequent to the`
  line `extended period:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any child admitted after the extended period shall complete his studies in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9023)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Examination and holding back in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9023&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Examination and holding back in certain cases.-- (1) There shall be a regular examination in`
  line `the fifth class and in the eighth class at the end of every academic year.`
  line
  line `(2) If a child fails in the examination referred to in sub-section (1), he shall be given additional`
  line `instruction and granted opportunity for re-examination within a period of two months from the date of`
  line `declaration of the result.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may allow schools to hold back a child in the fifth class or in the`
  line `eighth class or in both classes, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, if he`
  line `fails in the re-examination referred to in sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may decide not to hold back a child in any class till the`
  line `completion of elementary education.`
  line
  line `(4) No child shall be expelled from a school till the completion of elementary education.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 16, Central Act No. 35 of 2009.- In section 16 of the principal Act, for the`
  line `existing punctuation mark”. “appearing at the end, the punctuation mark”: “shall be substituted and`
  line `thereafter the following proviso shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `“Provided that if a child has not achieved class appropriate learning level in a class, he may be held`
  line `back in that class.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 2017, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9024)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Prohibition of physical punishment and mental harassment to child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9024&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No child shall be`
  line `subjected to physical punishment or mental harassment.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be liable to disciplinary action under`
  line `the service rules applicable to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9025)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `No school to be established without obtaining certificate of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9025&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No school, other`
  line `than a school established, owned or controlled by the appropriate Government or the local authority, shall,`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, be established or function, without obtaining a certificate of`
  line `recognition from such authority, by making an application in such form and manner, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `(2) The authority prescribed under sub-section (1) shall issue the certificate of recognition in such`
  line `form, within such period, in such manner, and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that no such recognition shall be granted to a school unless it fulfils norms and standards`
  line `specified under section 19.`
  line `(3) On the contravention of the conditions of recognition, the prescribed authority shall, by an order`
  line `in writing, withdraw recognition:`
  line `Provided that such order shall contain a direction as to which of the neighbourhood school, the`
  line `children studying in the derecognised school, shall be admitted:`
  line `Provided further that no recognition shall be so withdrawn without giving an opportunity of being`
  line `heard to such school, in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line `(4) With effect from the date of withdrawal of the recognition under sub-section (3), no such school`
  line `shall continue to function.`
  line `(5) Any person who establishes or runs a school without obtaining certificate of recognition, or`
  line `continues to run a school after withdrawal of recognition, shall be liable to fine which may extend to one`
  line `lakh rupees and in case of continuing contraventions, to a fine of ten thousand rupees for each day during`
  line `which such contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9026)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Norms and standards for school.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9026&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No school shall be established, or recognised, under`
  line `section 18, unless it fulfils the norms and standards specified in the Schedule.`
  line `(2) Where a school established before the commencement of this Act does not fulfil the norms and`
  line `standards specified in the Schedule, it shall take steps to fulfil such norms and standards at its own`
  line `expenses, within a period of three years from the date of such commencement.`
  line `(3) Where a school fails to fulfil the norms and standards within the period specified under subsection`
  line `(2), the authority prescribed under sub-section (1) of section 18 shall withdraw recognition`
  line `granted to such school in the manner specified under sub-section (3) thereof.`
  line `(4) With effect from the date of withdrawal of recognition under sub-section (3), no school shall`
  line `continue to function.`
  line `(5) Any person who continues to run a school after the recognition is withdrawn, shall be liable to`
  line `fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and in case of continuing contraventions, to a fine of ten`
  line `thousand rupees for each day during which such contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9027)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9027&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, amend the Schedule`
  line `by adding to, or omitting therefrom, any norms and standards.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9028)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `School Management Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2012, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-2012)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9028&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) A school, other than a school specified in sub-clause (iv)`
  line `of clause (n) of section 2, shall constitute a School Management Committee consisting of the elected`
  line `representatives of the local authority, parents or guardians of children admitted in such school and`
  line `teachers:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least three-fourth of members of such Committee shall be parents or guardians:`
  line
  line `Provided further that proportionate representation shall be given to the parents or guardians of`
  line `children belonging to disadvantaged group and weaker section:`
  line
  line `Provided also that fifty per cent. of Members of such Committee shall be women.`
  line
  line `(2) The School Management Committee shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) monitor the working of the school;`
  line
  line `(b) prepare and recommend school development plan;`
  line
  line `(c) monitor the utilisation of the grants received from the appropriate Government or local`
  line `authority or any other source; and`
  line
  line `(d) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the School Management Committee constituted under sub-section (1) in respect of,--`
  line
  line `(a) a school established and administered by minority whether based on religion or language; and`
  line
  line `(b) all other aided schools as defined in sub-section (ii) of clause (n) of section 2,`
  line
  line `shall perform advisory function only.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21, Central Act No. 35 of 2009.—In sub-section (2) of section 21 of the`
  line `principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (c), the existing word “and”, appearing at the end, shall be deleted; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after the existing clause (c), so amended, and before the existing clause (d), the following new`
  line `clause shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `“(ca) ensure that teachers perform their duties specified by or under section 24; and”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 2017, s. 4.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9029)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `School Development Plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "School Management Committee, constituted" (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9029&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every ^1[School Management Committee, except the School`
  line `Management Committee in respect of a school established and administered by minority, whether based`
  line `on religion or language and an aided school as defined in sub-clause (ii) of clause (n) of section 2,`
  line `constituted] under sub-section (1) of section 21, shall prepare a School Development Plan, in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The School Development Plan so prepared under sub-section (1) shall be the basis for the plans`
  line `and grants to be made by the appropriate Government or local authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9030)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Qualifications for appointment and terms and conditions of service of teachers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 24 of 2017, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9030&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `person possessing such minimum qualifications, as laid down by an academic authority, authorised by the`
  line `Central Government, by notification, shall be eligible for appointment as a teacher.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a State does not have adequate institutions offering courses or training in teacher`
  line `education, or teachers possessing minimum qualifications as laid down under sub-section (1) are not`
  line `available in sufficient numbers, the Central Government may, if it deems necessary, by notification, relax`
  line `the minimum qualifications required for appointment as a teacher, for such period, not exceeding five`
  line `years, as may be specified in that notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that a teacher who, at the commencement of this Act, does not possess minimum`
  line `qualifications as laid down under sub-section (1), shall acquire such minimum qualifications within a`
  line `period of five years.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that every teacher appointed or in position as on the 31st March, 2015, who does`
  line `not possess minimum qualifications as laid down under sub-section (1), shall acquire such minimum`
  line `qualifications within a period of four years from the date of commencement of the Right of Children to`
  line `Free and Compulsory Education (Amendment) Act, 2017 (24 of 2017).]`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to, and the terms and conditions of service of, teachers shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (9031)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Duties of teachers and redressal of grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9031&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) A teacher appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 23 shall perform the following duties, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain regularity and punctuality in attending school;`
  line
  line `(b) conduct and complete the curriculum in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 29;`
  line
  line `(c) complete entire curriculum within the specified time;`
  line
  line `(d) assess the learning ability of each child and accordingly supplement additional instructions, if`
  line `any, as required;`
  line
  line `(e) hold regular meetings with parents and guardians and apprise them about the regularity in`
  line `attendance, ability to learn, progress made in learning and any other relevant information about the`
  line `child; and`
  line
  line `(f) perform such other duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A teacher committing default in performance of duties specified in sub-section (1), shall be liable`
  line `to disciplinary action under the service rules applicable to him or her:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking such disciplinary action, reasonable opportunity of being heard shall be`
  line `afforded to such teacher.`
  line
  line `(3) The grievances, if any, of the teacher shall be redressed in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 24, Central Act No. 35 of 2009.-In clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `24 of the principal Act, for the existing expression “as required”, the expression “required for achieving`
  line `class appropriate learning level” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 2017, s. 5.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (9032)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Pupil-Teacher Ratio.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 30 of 2012, s. 7, for "Within six months" (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9032&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Within three years] from the date of commencement of this Act, the`
  line `appropriate Government and the local authority shall ensure that the Pupil-Teacher Ratio, as specified in`
  line `the Schedule, is maintained in each school.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of maintaining the Pupil-Teacher Ratio under sub-section (1), no teacher posted in`
  line `a school shall be made to serve in any other school or office or deployed for any non-educational purpose,`
  line `other than those specified in section 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (9033)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Filling up vacancies of teachers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9033&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The appointing authority, in relation to a school established,`
  line `owned, controlled or substantially financed by funds provided directly or indirectly by the appropriate`
  line `Government or by a local authority, shall ensure that vacancy of teacher in a school under its control shall`
  line `not exceed ten per cent/of the total sanctioned strength.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (9034)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prohibition of deployment of teachers for non-educational purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9034&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No teacher shall be`
  line `deployed for any non-educational purposes other than the decennial population census, disaster relief`
  line `duties or duties relating to elections to the local authority or the State Legislatures or Parliament, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (9035)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Prohibition of private tuition by teacher.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9035&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No teacher shall engage himself or herself in private`
  line `tuition or private teaching activity.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (9036)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Curriculum and evaluation procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9036&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The curriculum and the evaluation procedure for`
  line `elementary education shall be laid down by an academic authority to be specified by the appropriate`
  line `Government, by notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The academic authority, while laying down the curriculum and the evaluation procedure under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall take into consideration the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) conformity with the values enshrined in the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) all round development of the child;`
  line
  line `(c) building up child's knowledge, potentiality and talent;`
  line
  line `(d) development of physical and mental abilities to the fullest extent;`
  line
  line `(e) learning through activities, discovery and exploration in a child friendly and child-centered`
  line manner;
  line
  line `(f) medium of instructions shall, as far as practicable, be in child's mother tongue;`
  line
  line `(g) making the child free of fear, trauma and anxiety and helping the child to express views`
  line freely;
  line
  line `(h) comprehensive and continuous evaluation of child's understanding of knowledge and his or`
  line `her ability to apply the same.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 29, Central Act No. 35 of 2009.—In sub-section (1) of section 29 of the`
  line `principal Act, after the existing expression “curriculum” and before the existing expression “and the evaluation`
  line `procedure”, the expression”, class appropriate learning level” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 32 of 2017, s. 6.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (9037)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Examination and completion certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9037&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No child shall be required to pass any Board`
  line `examination till completion of elementary education.`
  line
  line `(2) Every child completing his elementary education shall be awarded a certificate, in such form and`
  line `in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (9038)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Monitoring of child’s right to education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9038&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 3, or, as the case may be, the State Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 17, of the Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006), shall, in addition to the functions assigned to them under that Act, also perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) examine and review the safeguards for rights provided by or under this Act and recommend`
  line `measures for their effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(b) inquire into complaints relating to child's right to free and compulsory education; and`
  line
  line `(c) take necessary steps as provided under sections 15 and 24 of the said Commissions for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Commissions shall, while inquiring into any matters relating to child's right to free and`
  line `compulsory education under clause (c) of sub-section (1), have the same powers as assigned to them`
  line `respectively under sections 14 and 24 of the said Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the State Commission for Protection of Child Rights has not been constituted in a State, the`
  line `appropriate Government may, for the purpose of performing the functions specified in clauses (a) to (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1), constitute such authority, in such manner and subject to such terms and conditions, as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (9039)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Redressal of grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9039&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 31, any person`
  line `having any grievance relating to the right of a child under this Act may make a written complaint to the`
  line `local authority having jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) After receiving the complaint under sub-section (1), the local authority shall decide the matter`
  line `within a period of three months after affording a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the parties`
  line concerned.
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by the decision of the local authority may prefer an appeal to the State`
  line `Commission for Protection of Child Rights or the authority prescribed under sub-section (3) of section 31,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The appeal preferred under sub-section (3) shall be decided by State Commission for Protection of`
  line `Child Rights or the authority prescribed under sub-section (3) of section 31, as the case may be, as`
  line `provided under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (9040)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Constitution of National Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9040&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute, by`
  line `notification, a National Advisory Council, consisting of such number of Members, not exceeding fifteen,`
  line `as the Central Government may deem necessary, to be appointed from amongst persons having`
  line `knowledge and practical experience in the field of elementary education and child development.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the National Advisory Council shall be to advise the Central Government on`
  line `implementation of the provisions of the Act in an effective manner.`
  line
  line `(3) The allowances and other terms and conditions of the appointment of Members of the National`
  line `Advisory Council shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (9041)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Constitution of State Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9041&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall constitute, by`
  line `notification, a State Advisory Council consisting of such number of Members, not exceeding fifteen, as`
  line `the State Government may deem necessary, to be appointed from amongst persons having knowledge and`
  line `practical experience in the field of elementary education and child development.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the State Advisory council shall be to advise the State Government on`
  line `implementation of the provisions of the Act in an effective manner.`
  line
  line `(3) The allowances and other terms and conditions of appointment of Members of the State Advisory`
  line `Council shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (9042)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9042&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may issue such guidelines to the`
  line `appropriate Government or, as the case may be, the local authority, as it deems fit for the purposes of`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may issue guidelines and give such directions, as it deems fit, to the`
  line `local authority or the School Management Committee regarding implementation of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) The local authority may issue guidelines and give such directions, as it deems fit, to the School`
  line `Management Committee regarding implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (9043)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Previous sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9043&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for offences punishable under sub-section`
  line `(2) of section 13, sub-section (5) of section 18 and sub-section (5) of section 19 shall be instituted except`
  line `with the previous sanction of an officer authorised in this behalf, by the appropriate Government, by`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (9044)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9044&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government, the State Government, the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights, the`
  line `State Commission for Protection of Child Rights, the local authority, the School Management Committee`
  line `or any person, in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done, in pursuance of`
  line `this Act, or any rules or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (9045)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9045&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules, for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of giving special training and the time-limit thereof, under first proviso to`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the area or limits for establishment of a neighbourhood school, under section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of maintenance of records of children up to the age of fourteen years, under`
  line `clause (d) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner and extent of reimbursement of expenditure, under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) any other document for determining the age of child under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) the extended period for admission and the manner of completing study if admitted after the`
  line `extended period, under section 15;`
  line
  line `^1[(fa) the manner and the conditions subject to which a child may be held back under sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 16;]`
  line
  line `(g) the authority, the form and manner of making application for certificate of recognition, under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(h) the form, the period, the manner and the conditions for issuing certificate of recognition,`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of giving opportunity of hearing under second proviso to sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(j) the Other functions to be performed by School Management Committee under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of preparing School Development Plan under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(l) the salary and allowances payable to, and the terms and conditions of service of, teacher, under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(m) the duties to be performed by the teacher under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of redressing grievances of teachers under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(o) the form and manner of awarding certificate for completion of elementary education under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(p) the authority, the manner of its constitution and the terms and conditions therefor, under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(q) the allowances and other terms and conditions of appointment of Members of the National`
  line `Advisory Council under sub-section (3) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(r) the allowances and other terms and conditions of appointment of Members of the State`
  line `Advisory Council under sub-section (3) of section 34.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act and every notification issued under sections 20 and 23 by the`
  line `Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made, the rule or notification shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule or notification made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made; before the State Legislatures.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (9046)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Central Government to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 30 of 2012, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595&sectionId=9046&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_9_00006_200935_1517807327595
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Power of Central Government to remove difficulties.-- (1) If any difficulty arises in giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be`
  line `necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education (Amendment) Act, 2012`
  line `(30 of 2012).`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.]`
